---
import BaseLayout from "../../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "About Me | Jair Revilla";
const description =
  "Moodle Architect and Developer specializing in performance, integrations, and custom plugins.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} lang="en">
  <main class="container">
    <section class="about-section">
      <h1 class="page-title">About Me</h1>

      <div class="content">
        <div class="profile-header">
          <h2>Hello, I'm Jair Edson Revilla Arroyo</h2>
          <p class="lead">
            I am a software developer specialized in <strong
              >E-learning with Moodle</strong
            >, with a career focused on building <strong
              >stable, secure, and scalable</strong
            > platforms: from full implementations, controlled upgrades, and high-availability
            architectures, to <strong>custom plugins</strong> and <strong
              >enterprise integrations</strong
            > with academic systems (SIS/ERP).
          </p>
          <p>
            My approach is 100% professional: I prioritize operational
            continuity, quality, maintainability, and clear deliverables
            (documentation, runbooks, QA evidence, and traceability).
          </p>
        </div>

        <hr />

        <h2>What I do (and why it works)</h2>

        <div class="feature-block">
          <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-gauge-high"></i> High Concurrency Moodle
          </h3>
          <p>
            I design and optimize Moodle for critical scenarios: <strong
              >enrollment spikes</strong
            > and <strong>simultaneous exams</strong>, taking care of every
            layer (DB, caching, PHP-FPM, storage, cron/adhoc tasks) and adding
            observability to detect degradation before it becomes an incident.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-block">
          <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-network-wired"></i> Architecture & High Availability
          </h3>
          <p>
            I have implemented Moodle prepared for <strong
              >High Availability</strong
            > on <strong>Huawei Cloud</strong> for sensitive environments (e.g., exam
            platforms).
          </p>
          <p>
            I work with resilience patterns: load balancing, horizontal scaling,
            separation of concerns, and real backup/restore strategies.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-block">
          <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-plug-circle-bolt"></i> SIS/ERP Integrations (REST/Web
            Services)
          </h3>
          <p>
            I automate academic processes end-to-end: <strong
              >users, courses, sections, enrollments, certificates</strong
            >, with traceability, idempotency, and controlled retries. I have
            integrated Moodle with systems like <strong>Banner</strong>, <strong
              >PeopleSoft</strong
            >, and internal platforms via Web Services.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-block">
          <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-puzzle-piece"></i> Custom Moodle Plugin Development
          </h3>
          <p>
            I develop <strong
              >mod / block / local / enrol / auth / report</strong
            > plugins following best practices:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>capabilities and permissions per context</li>
            <li>events, logs, and auditing</li>
            <li>Privacy API when applicable</li>
            <li>compatibility with backup/restore</li>
            <li>performance (pagination, MUC cache, cron jobs)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This allows building "business" functionalities without hacks and
            with a sustainable base for upgrades.
          </p>
        </div>

        <hr />

        <h2>Representative Projects</h2>
        <p>
          Over the years, I have participated in initiatives for institutions
          and companies, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>
            Implementations and upgrades on modern versions (e.g., <strong
              >Moodle 4.4</strong
            > and major upgrades).
          </li>
          <li>
            Implementations with <strong>high-availability architecture</strong> (Huawei
            Cloud) for critical scenarios like exams.
          </li>
          <li>
            Moodle-based app with <strong>branding</strong> ready for publication
            (Android/iOS).
          </li>
          <li>
            "<strong>Aprendo en Casa</strong>" case (offline Moodle app at code
            level for special functional requirements).
          </li>
          <li>
            Plugin improvements (e.g., Zoom: recordings + meeting
            massification).
          </li>
          <li>
            Legacy integrations with SIS (e.g., PeopleSoft, Socrates) automating
            creation/update and enrollment.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <hr />

        <h2>How I Work</h2>
        <div class="work-method-grid">
          <div class="method-item">
            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-diagram-project"></i> Method</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>Diagnosis</strong>: objectives, expected spikes, risks,
                plugin/integration inventory.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Actionable Plan</strong>: quick wins + roadmap
                (30/60/90), with impact and prioritization.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Controlled Implementation</strong>: DEV/UAT/PROD,
                checklist, evidence, and rollback.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Operation</strong>: monitoring, runbooks, preventive
                maintenance, and support during critical events.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="method-item">
            <h3>
              <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved"></i> Security by Default
            </h3>
            <ul>
              <li>least privilege (roles/capabilities)</li>
              <li>server and application hardening</li>
              <li>change control and auditing</li>
              <li>
                secure integrations (tokens/signatures, idempotency, retries)
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr />

        <h2>Technical Stack</h2>
        <ul class="tags-list">
          <li><strong>Moodle / PHP / MySQL</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Linux</strong> (AWS AMI, CentOS, Ubuntu, Rocky)</li>
          <li>
            <strong>AWS</strong> (EC2, RDS, S3) and <strong
              >Huawei Cloud</strong>
          </li>
          <li><strong>Docker</strong></li>
          <li>Integrations and backend: <strong>Laravel / Lumen</strong></li>
          <li>Agile approach: <strong>Scrum</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <hr />

        <h2>Certifications</h2>
        <ul class="cert-list">
          <li>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-certificate"></i>
            <strong>Moodle Developer</strong> Certification
          </li>
          <li>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-certificate"></i> Scrum Fundamentals / Scrum Master
            (ScrumStudy)
          </li>
        </ul>

        <hr />

        <div class="cta-block">
          <h2>What can you expect when working with me?</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Clear deliverables (documentation + runbook + evidence).</li>
            <li>Robust solutions (no "patches").</li>
            <li>Focus on continuity and real performance.</li>
            <li>Direct communication and results orientation.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-section">
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you need to implement, optimize, or scale your Moodle (or
            integrate it with your SIS/ERP), let's talk.
          </p>
          <a href="/en/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Go to Contact</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-section {
    padding: var(--space-8) 0;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    color: #1a1a1a;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .content {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #333;
  }

  .content h2 {
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-size: 1.8rem;
  }

  .content h3 {
    color: #2c3e50;
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .content h3 i {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .content p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .content ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .content li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  hr {
    border: 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: #eee;
    margin: var(--space-10) 0;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #444;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .feature-block {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  /* Lists Styling */
  .check-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .check-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 25px;
  }
  .check-list li:before {
    content: "âœ“";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .tags-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .tags-list li {
    background: #f0f0f0;
    padding: 5px 15px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cert-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .cta-block {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
  }
  .cta-block h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .contact-section {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    background: #eef2f5;
    padding: var(--space-8);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }
  .contact-section h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .contact-section .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }
</style>
